<div id="wrapper"><h2><a href="/output/Page2.asp"><img alt="" height="70" src="../files/images/XM_logo.gif" title="XM London Digital Communication" width="162" /></a></h2><h2><img width="190" alt="Case histories" height="80" border="0" src="/files/images/XM_L3_Clients_histories_shdr.gif" /></h2><p><strong>i-uk</strong></p><p>I-uk.com is an information Portal for overseas visitors wishing to find out about the UK.</p><p>The Partners involved include the British Tourist Authority, British Council, Trade Partners, Invest UK, BBC World Service and the Foreign Office.</p><p>It aggregates links to sites and sets them in context around identified user needs, delivering a wealth of information on business, travel, education and UK culture.</p><p>Workshops were held with all Partners to socialise the solution and to ensure internal buy-in.</p><p>It was important to consider accessibility for the wide overseas audience including technical, cultural and language variations.</p><p><a href="http://www.i-uk.com">http://www.i-uk.com</a></p><p><img alt="i-uk" border="0" height="210" src="/files/images/i-uk 1.jpg" width="275" /></p><p> <img alt="i-uk" border="0" height="211" src="/files/images/i-uk 2.jpg" width="275" /></p><img class="hide" src="/files/images/clear.gif" width="1" height="1" alt="" />
